# Auto-HTTPS frontend for the Dealer's Choice server-list widget.
#
# Caddy obtains and renews a Let's Encrypt certificate for $DC_WEB_DOMAIN
# automatically. With only port 443 open it uses the TLS-ALPN-01 challenge, so
# no port 80 is required.
#
# The page (server-list.html, mounted as /site/index.html) and the registry's
# servers.json (its dir mounted read-only at /json) come from two SEPARATE mounts
# -- a file can't be mounted inside a read-only dir mount -- so they're served
# from one origin here: /servers.json from /json, everything else from /site.
# Same origin, so the page needs no CORS.
#
# Requirements: DC_WEB_DOMAIN set, and a DNS A record pointing it at this host.
{$DC_WEB_DOMAIN} {
	handle /servers.json {
		root * /json
		file_server
	}
	handle {
		root * /site
		file_server
	}
}
